Installed-Size: 8541
Depends: haddock-interface-31
Section: doc
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://propellor.branchable.com/
Description: property-based host configuration management in haskell; documentation
 Propellor ensures that the system it's run in satisfies a list of
 properties, taking action as necessary when a property is not yet met.
 .
 It is configured using haskell.
 .
 The easiest way to get started with propellor is to install the binary package
 `propellor' and run `propellor --init'.
 .
 This package provides the documentation for a library for the Haskell
 programming language.
 See http://www.haskell.org/ for more information on Haskell.
